when a task depends on another task being completed

scheduling becomes intractible when some tasks depend on other tasks or some tasks cannot be done until a specific time. 9% of scheduling can be solved and 90% proven intractible

being able to stop a task to work on another task makes the problem tractible: when a task's starting time comes, compare that task to the one currently underway. work on the one with the earliest due date, or the one that can be completed first if working on shortest processing time
as soon as task comes in, divide its weight by time to complete and switch to it if greater than that value for the currently being worked on task.
note: knowing all this ahead of time makes the problem intractible, but deciding as things comes in yields this optimal strategy. clairvoyance can be a burden!
